         <abstract>
            <p>A new approach to the construction of finite-difference methods is presented. It is shown how the multi-point differentiators can generate regularizing algorithms with a stepsize h being a regularization parameter. The explicitly computable estimation constants are given. Also an iteratively regularized scheme for solving the numerical differentiation problem in the form of Volterra integral equation is developed.</p>
